my world.

142
00:06:11,003 --> 00:06:12,312
<i>Dr. Gruber to the OR.</i>

143
00:06:12,397 --> 00:06:14,237
- Helm, what do we got?
<i>- Dr. Gruber to the OR.</i>

144
00:06:14,332 --> 00:06:18,341
Byron Gibbis, 52, found
passed out on his front porch.

145
00:06:18,426 --> 00:06:20,778
He's febrile, tachycardic.
I also heard a big murmur.

146
00:06:20,863 --> 00:06:22,216
Rapid COVID was negative,

147
00:06:22,301 --> 00:06:24,474
no signs of head trauma,
but I did order a pan scan.

148
00:06:24,559 --> 00:06:25,848
Let's add a cardiac CT.

149
00:06:25,957 --> 00:06:27,614
Um, do you work here?

150
00:06:27,699 --> 00:06:28,724
Dr. Winston Ndugu,

151
00:06:28,809 --> 00:06:30,325
cardiothoracic surgeon
from Tufts.

152
00:06:30,416 --> 00:06:32,059
He's got Osler's nodes.

153
00:06:36,023 --> 00:06:38,289
Oh, my God.
My God.

154
00:06:38,373 --> 00:06:40,670
Byron, I'm Dr. Maggie Pierce.
You're at Grey-Sloan Memorial.

155
00:06:40,754 --> 00:06:42,061
You were found unconscious,
and an ambulance...

156
00:06:42,145 --> 00:06:43,044
- Get away from me!
- Okay...

157
00:06:43,129 --> 00:06:44,506
No, I'm serious.
Everybody back up, okay?

158
00:06:44,590 --> 00:06:46,162
I'm not getting COVID.
Where are my clothes?

159
00:06:46,246 --> 00:06:48,386
- Sir, please just...
- Everybody here is sick.

160
00:06:48,470 --> 00:06:49,606
Oh, God.

161
00:06:49,691 --> 00:06:51,880
Okay, Byron,
I know that this is a shock

162
00:06:51,965 --> 00:06:53,208
and I know
that you're scared,

163
00:06:53,293 --> 00:06:54,615
but if we don't get
a look at your heart,

164
00:06:54,699 --> 00:06:55,966
you may not make it home.

165
00:06:56,051 --> 00:06:57,372
We have all been tested.

166
00:06:57,457 --> 00:06:59,536
If you need a mask
or if you need a face shield,

167
00:06:59,621 --> 00:07:00,764
we can get you
whatever you need.

168
00:07:00,848 --> 00:07:02,748
But, please, just stay.

169
00:07:02,832 --> 00:07:04,434
I was so good.

170
00:07:04,660 --> 00:07:05,795
I didn't go anywhere.

171
00:07:05,879 --> 00:07:07,441
Let's get you ready
for CT.

172
00:07:10,361 --> 00:07:14,286
One minute I'm sad,
'cause I think about his sister

173
00:07:14,371 --> 00:07:17,328
and his family
and what a great guy he was.

174
00:07:17,902 --> 00:07:19,809
Next minute,
I'm filled with guilt.

175
00:07:19,893 --> 00:07:21,158
Then I'm filled with rage.

176
00:07:21,292 --> 00:07:22,801
That a person could

177
00:07:24,027 --> 00:07:26,949
Do that
to another human being.

178
00:07:27,379 --> 00:07:30,403
I'm scared. Hopeless.
Sometimes numb.

179
00:07:30,488 --> 00:07:32,075
I can always go back
to guilt.

180
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:34,041
Guilt is my go-to.

181
00:07:34,457 --> 00:07:37,044
My go-to is numb.

182
00:07:37,128 --> 00:07:38,816
Wow.

183
00:07:39,130 --> 00:07:41,692
Did you just describe
exactly what was wrong

184
00:07:41,777 --> 00:07:43,685
with our relationship
in only five words?

185
00:07:45,136 --> 00:07:47,419
I think maybe
I just did.

186
00:07:50,706 --> 00:07:53,152
I just...
DeLuca. I...

187
00:07:56,275 --> 00:07:59,017
I-I just can't
get my head around it.

188
00:08:06,652 --> 00:08:08,504
What is this?

189
00:08:09,285 --> 00:08:10,729
Looks like whiskey.

190
00:08:10,813 --> 00:08:12,879
Mm, what was it doing

191
00:08:12,965 --> 00:08:15,169
on the top shelf behind
the fancy candlesticks?

192
00:08:15,253 --> 00:08:16,786
What were you doing
on the top shelf

193
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:17,910
behind the fancy
candlesticks?

194
00:08:17,994 --> 00:08:19,173
Are you drunk?

195
00:08:19,257 --> 00:08:20,488
It's 9:00 in the morning.

196
00:08:20,606 --> 00:08:22,132
Plenty of people get drunk
at 9:00 in the morning.

197
00:08:22,216 --> 00:08:24,840
Yeah, well, not me,
Amelia.

198
00:08:25,042 --> 00:08:27,006
I live at home
with four kids.

199
00:08:27,091 --> 00:08:29,531
Sometimes late at night...

200
00:08:29,615 --> 00:08:31,663
...I have a drink in the garage
and I play my guitar.

201
00:08:31,747 --> 00:08:32,925
We're in a pandemic.

202
00:08:33,009 --> 00:08:35,667
You drink in the garage?
Do you hear yourself?

203
00:08:35,751 --> 00:08:37,177
Do youhear yourself?

204
00:08:37,262 --> 00:08:39,583
Hiding alcohol
is an objectively bad sign.

205
00:08:39,668 --> 00:08:41,586
Or it's a sign that I'm trying
to be respectful of you.

206
00:08:41,670 --> 00:08:43,414
If you have a problem,
you can talk to me.

207
00:08:43,498 --> 00:08:45,851
I'm, like, literally
the best person in the world

208
00:08:45,935 --> 00:08:48,074
- you could talk to.
- Do you know stressed out I am?

209
00:08:48,158 --> 00:08:49,107
All the time?

210
00:08:49,191 --> 00:08:51,037
And now on top of everything,
if it wasn't hard enough,

211
00:08:51,121 --> 00:08:53,163
now I have to make sure that
I don't accidentally mention

212
00:08:53,247 --> 00:08:55,145
that their friend Andrew
was stabbed to death

213
00:08:55,230 --> 00:08:56,895
by somebody
who sells children for sex.

214
00:08:56,980 --> 00:08:58,958
Okay, that is all of us.
That is not just you.

215
00:08:59,043 --> 00:09:01,345
And not all of us
have to drink to cope.

216
00:09:01,504 --> 00:09:03,317
You don't have to,
or you don't get to?

217
00:09:03,402 --> 00:09:06,012
Because I get to.
Because I'm not an alcoholic.

218
00:09:06,110 --> 00:09:07,373
I'm not in recovery and...

219
00:09:08,915 --> 00:09:10,262
Y'know what?

220
00:09:10,743 --> 00:09:12,293
I can't be here right now.

221
00:09:12,378 --> 00:09:14,270
- You're leaving?
- Yes.

222
00:09:14,355 --> 00:09:16,256
