So serious.

248
00:10:28,902 --> 00:10:30,826
Then she gets that
worried little brow.

249
00:10:33,738 --> 00:10:35,439
This is torture!

250
00:10:35,523 --> 00:10:37,145
You're right here,
and I can't...

251
00:10:37,230 --> 00:10:38,364
It's torture!

252
00:10:38,449 --> 00:10:40,227
It's a torture
of your own devising.

253
00:10:40,311 --> 00:10:42,170
You were always good at that.

254
00:10:42,254 --> 00:10:43,491
Good at what?

255
00:10:43,575 --> 00:10:44,973
Torturing yourself.

256
00:10:45,059 --> 00:10:47,552
I don't do that
as much anymore.

257
00:10:52,539 --> 00:10:54,786
You never got to meet Ellis.

258
00:10:54,871 --> 00:10:56,247
We didn't even know.

259
00:10:56,332 --> 00:10:58,160
I wish
you got to know her.

260
00:10:58,487 --> 00:11:00,238
She looks just like you.

261
00:11:00,387 --> 00:11:02,466
She breaks the rules
just like you.

262
00:11:02,551 --> 00:11:05,904
And she's quick to anger.
And quick to laugh.

263
00:11:05,988 --> 00:11:11,387
And she's smart and pensive
and stubborn, just like you.

264
00:11:12,777 --> 00:11:15,950
Hates pink and purple,
loves brown and green,

265
00:11:16,035 --> 00:11:18,044
and... and gets enraged
at the thought

266
00:11:18,129 --> 00:11:20,129
of anybody wanting to
cut down a tree.

267
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:29,521
Is... Is this thing clean?

268
00:11:29,605 --> 00:11:31,927
People say you can't get sick
from surfaces, but you can.

269
00:11:32,012 --> 00:11:34,513
We thoroughly disinfect
the entire room

270
00:11:34,598 --> 00:11:35,645
in between patients.

271
00:11:35,730 --> 00:11:38,060
- Sir?
- Just... I need a minute, okay?

272
00:11:38,145 --> 00:11:40,122
Can I leave my face shield on,
please?

273
00:11:40,207 --> 00:11:41,809
- Sure.
- Oh, God.

274
00:11:42,949 --> 00:11:44,966
If you'd like,
I can stay with you.

275
00:11:45,051 --> 00:11:46,395
- I can hold your foot or...
- No, no, no, no. I don't want

276
00:11:46,479 --> 00:11:48,614
anybody touching me.
Nobody touches me, okay?

277
00:11:48,699 --> 00:11:51,731
Osler's nodes,
so... endocarditis.

278
00:11:51,816 --> 00:11:54,074
Yes, but what is
the underlying cause?

279
00:11:54,262 --> 00:11:55,802
He denies
intravenous drug use,

280
00:11:55,887 --> 00:11:58,403
there's no indwelling catheter,
no diabetes...

281
00:11:58,488 --> 00:12:01,020
He said he hasn't left his house
since lockdown, right?

282
00:12:01,105 --> 00:12:02,231
May I?

283
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:06,004
- Hey, Byron.
- Yeah?

284
00:12:06,089 --> 00:12:08,435
Have you had any trouble
with your teeth lately?

285
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:11,544
I had a... a popcorn kernel
stuck in my teeth,

286
00:12:11,629 --> 00:12:12,732
and I picked it out
with a paperclip

287
00:12:12,816 --> 00:12:14,560
and... and now my gums
are a little sore,

288
00:12:14,645 --> 00:12:15,920
but I-I'm not going
to the dentist.

289
00:12:16,004 --> 00:12:17,873
I'm not gonna lay there with
my mouth open for 20 minutes

290
00:12:17,957 --> 00:12:19,170
inhaling somebody's
spit droplets.

291
00:12:19,254 --> 00:12:20,770
- No way.
- Bingo.

292
00:12:20,855 --> 00:12:24,340
Dental infection, which led
to bacterial endocarditis.

293
00:12:24,980 --> 00:12:28,691
Aortic valve abscess almost
completely blocking the valves.

294
00:12:28,776 --> 00:12:31,215
Helm, order some antibiotics
and book an OR.

295
00:12:32,973 --> 00:12:34,586
I thought of it.

296
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:36,013
You just said it first.

297
00:12:36,098 --> 00:12:38,111
Oh, yeah, I believe you.

298
00:12:38,196 --> 00:12:39,850
100%.

299
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:46,468
Were you looking
for me, dear?

300
00:12:46,676 --> 00:12:48,156
Yeah, I was.
Yeah.

301
00:12:53,043 --> 00:12:55,216
You know, I built my life,

302
00:12:55,386 --> 00:12:57,215
my sanity,

303
00:12:57,332 --> 00:12:59,828
my sobriety...

304
00:13:00,309 --> 00:13:03,332
around the surrender
to a higher power.

305
00:13:03,660 --> 00:13:04,878
I mean, for me,

306
00:13:04,962 --> 00:13:08,882
it's the belief
that there's some purpose.

307
00:13:08,966 --> 00:13:14,017
That there's
a... a bigger plan.

308
00:13:14,101 --> 00:13:17,785
Something that if
I got all the way above it

309
00:13:17,926 --> 00:13:20,121
and could look down on it

310
00:13:20,473 --> 00:13:21,764
like, um...

311
00:13:21,849 --> 00:13:24,513
- like a jigsaw puzzle, okay?
- Mm.

312
00:13:24,676 --> 00:13:27,335
That somehow it would...
it would make sense.

313
00:13:27,419 --> 00:13:29,990
My faith is rooted
in the trust

314
00:13:30,074 --> 00:13:34,342
that there's a... a meaning
and a wisdom

315
00:13:35,371 --> 00:13:38,912
that I'm just not elevated
enough to see or understand.

316
00:13:39,168 --> 00:13:42,809
A faith that
whoever made this puzzle,

317
00:13:43,363 --> 00:13:45,176
it makes sense to Him.

318
00:13:46,379 --> 00:13:48,512
- And it's beautiful.
- Mm.

319
00:13:50,901 --> 00:13:52,927
Today,
I'm... I'm struggling.

320
00:13:53,012 --> 00:13:55,972
I'm struggling
with my faith.

321
00:13:56,056 --> 00:13:58,754
I'm struggling
to trust anything.

322
00:14:00,582 --> 00:14:07,090
And I just cannot
see any wisdom in this.

323
00:14:10,629 --> 00:14:14,637
I live
with stage 4 cancer.

324
00:14:14,941 --> 00:14:18,038
A cancer
very few people survive.

325
00:14:18,285 --> 00:14:21,138
I just got the results
from my latest scan,

326
00:14:21,223 --> 00:14:24,043
and... nothing has grown.

327
00:14:25,782 --> 00:14:27,395
It makes no sense.

328
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:28,974
Everywhere we look,

329
00:14:29,059 --> 00:14:32,356
someone is dying
that was healthy yesterday.

330
00:14:32,441 --> 00:14:35,316
It makes no sense.

331
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:38,855
"Puzzle"
is the right word.

332
00:14:39,230 --> 00:14:45,674
You can look for the pain,
the lost, the unbearable.

333
00:14:45,973 --> 00:14:49,988
Or you can look
for the beauty, the grace...

334
00:14:50,582 --> 00:14:52,463
the miracle.

335
00:14:52,824 --> 00:14:55,738
And nothing grew?

336
00:14:56,598 --> 00:14:58,904
Nothing grew.

337
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:06,521
Okay, so, I know
that people buy and trade

338
00:15:06,605 --> 00:15:09,598
and get rich
and then just lose everything.

339
00:15:09,777 --> 00:15:12,488
But what exactly
is the stock market?

340
00:15:12,598 --> 00:15:14,958
It's a good thing you already
know how to live out of a car.

341
00:15:15,098 --> 00:15:16,653
Why? Well, questions like that

342
00:15:16,738 --> 00:15:18,154
make me think you're
gonna end up back in one.

343
00:15:21,871 --> 00:15:24,539
Uh...
who is it?

344
00:15:24,623 --> 00:15:26,628
It's Jackson Avery!

345
00:15:26,712 --> 00:15:28,282
I'm here for a quick bang.

346
00:15:28,366 --> 00:15:29,761
I...
Jo!

347
00:15:29,970 --> 00:15:31,015
I...

348
00:15:36,921 --> 00:15:38,600
Shut up.

349
00:15:38,685 --> 00:15:39,946
Bad time?

350
00:15:42,342 --> 00:15:44,565
Oh, crap.

351
00:15:44,810 --> 00:15:46,474
Hey. Really bad time.

352
00:15:46,558 --> 00:15:48,741
Um, I brought whiskey.

353
00:15:48,834 --> 00:15:51,459
Oh, we're day drinking.
Ah!

354
00:15:51,567 --> 00:15:53,578
Sorry, dude.
I didn't realize, uh...

355
00:15:53,662 --> 00:15:54,917
No, no, it's cool.

356
00:15:55,001 --> 00:15:57,577
Guess you're aware of our...
situation, then.

357
00:15:57,662 --> 00:15:59,553
Yep. Sweet deal.

358
00:16:01,302 --> 00:16:02,533
Here.

359
00:16:02,617 --> 00:16:03,926
Oh, no,
I'm on, uh, call.

360
00:16:04,010 --> 00:16:05,420
Oh! Dibs.

361
00:16:05,880 --> 00:16:07,936
Okay. Cheers.

362
00:16:08,021 --> 00:16:10,498
Happy...

363
00:16:10,731 --> 00:16:12,185
all-our-friends-are-dying
day.

364
00:16:19,112 --> 00:16:22,795
I told him we'd move as fast
as was safely possible.

365
00:16:22,888 --> 00:16:26,046
His echo showed
his ejection fraction at 64%,

366
00:16:26,131 --> 00:16:28,779
so hopefully his heart is strong
enough to have a good outcome.

367
00:16:28,881 --> 00:16:30,866
Who cleans his teeth
with a paperclip?

368
00:16:30,950 --> 00:16:33,717
Isolation makes people
do crazy things.

369
00:16:33,965 --> 00:16:35,428
We're not meant
to be alone.

370
00:16:36,131 --> 00:16:38,600
People physically
need people.

371
00:16:43,052 --> 00:16:45,272
Oh, no, no! Don't...
Don't... Don't touch me!

372
00:16:45,357 --> 00:16:47,873
Just back away!
Please, everybody, back away.

373
00:16:48,021 --> 00:16:50,031
- Dr. Pierce!
- I'm sorry. I can't be here!

374
00:16:50,115 --> 00:16:52,656
- I can't do this. I can't! Get away from me!
- Dr. Pierce. Dr. Pierce.

375
00:16:52,740 --> 00:16:54,656
- Dr. Pierce! A little help?
<i>- I can't be here! I can't be here!</i>

376
00:16:54,740 --> 00:16:56,558
- Oh, God.
- I can't! I can't be here.

377
00:16:56,643 --> 00:16:58,732
I can't.
I need to get out of here!

378
00:17:01,248 --> 00:17:03,716
Okay, call security.
I'm gonna go to the elevator.

379
00:17:03,827 --> 00:17:05,352
- You go to the OR board.
- I don't know where that is.

380
00:17:05,436 --> 00:17:07,225
- It's...
- Did anyone lose a naked man?

381
00:17:07,310 --> 00:17:08,677
Because he went that way.

382
00:17:08,911 --> 00:17:09,928
Oh.

383
00:17:14,180 --> 00:17:15,271
Byron?

384
00:17:25,435 --> 00:17:26,857
Hey, Byron.

385
00:17:26,942 --> 00:17:28,321
I'm... I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

386
00:17:30,481 --> 00:17:32,068
I can't do this.
I can't be here.

387
00:17:32,152 --> 00:17:33,553
I...

388
00:17:33,638 --> 00:17:36,121
Oh, my God, my masks.
I'm not wearing my masks.

389
00:17:36,206 --> 00:17:38,075
Honey, you're not wearing
anything.

390
00:17:43,474 --> 00:17:46,927
My best friend, Rory,
he was healthy as a horse.

391
00:17:47,348 --> 00:17:49,436
Never worked a day job
his entire life,

392
00:17:49,521 --> 00:17:50,538
he didn't smoke,
he didn't drink,

393
00:17:50,622 --> 00:17:51,837
he... he ran triathlons.

394
00:17:52,031 --> 00:17:54,471
He got the virus,
he was dead in a week. A week!

395
00:17:54,556 --> 00:17:56,388
Wife and kids didn't
get to say goodbye to him.

396
00:17:56,472 --> 00:17:57,737
Do you know
how many people

397
00:17:57,943 --> 00:17:59,513
they're projecting die
from this?

398
00:17:59,621 --> 00:18:02,018
- Hundreds of thousands.
- I know.

399
00:18:02,102 --> 00:18:04,560
And if you
want to walk out of here,

400
00:18:04,645 --> 00:18:06,021
I'm not gonna stop you.

401
00:18:06,275 --> 00:18:07,670
Wait, what?

402
00:18:07,755 --> 00:18:09,199
But I will follow you.

403
00:18:09,283 --> 00:18:11,244
Because your heart's
only gonna get worse,

404
00:18:11,328 --> 00:18:12,936
and I owe it to you,

405
00:18:13,021 --> 00:18:14,769
I owe it to my oath,

406
00:18:15,087 --> 00:18:16,419
I owe it...

407
00:18:19,596 --> 00:18:21,646
I lost someone, too,
Byron.

408
00:18:22,252 --> 00:18:23,739
Not COVID.

409
00:18:25,385 --> 00:18:27,042
But I know that pain,

410
00:18:27,127 --> 00:18:31,961
and I know how unfair it is
and how enraging it is.

411
00:18:32,045 --> 00:18:33,474
But I think...

412
00:18:35,936 --> 00:18:38,618
I think we owe it
to the people we lost

413
00:18:38,703 --> 00:18:40,578
to live the lives
that they can't.

414
00:18:40,662 --> 00:18:44,669
Even when it seems hard,
and even when we're afraid.

415
00:18:45,114 --> 00:18:48,064
Byron, you have a problem
that we can fix.

416
00:18:48,148 --> 00:18:49,413
We can fix this.

417
00:18:49,497 --> 00:18:50,849
But you have to let us.

418
00:18:50,933 --> 00:18:52,677
I don't want to die.

419
00:18:52,761 --> 00:18:53,895
I don't want to die.

420
00:18:53,979 --> 00:18:56,028
I don't want you to die,
either.

421
00:19:08,342 --> 00:19:09,692
Okay.

422
00:19:10,208 --> 00:19:11,348
Okay.

423
00:19:11,432 --> 00:19:14,220
Let's get you
a gown first.

424
00:19:14,304 --> 00:19:17,286
She didn't even know
that she was pregnant.

425
00:19:17,371 --> 00:19:18,636
And then
we saved her baby.

426
00:19:18,721 --> 00:19:20,334
And then...

427
00:19:20,419 --> 00:19:21,728
she died.

428
00:19:21,813 --> 00:19:23,905
It's like,
during a pandemic,

429
00:19:23,990 --> 00:19:26,866
shouldn't all the other
tragic crap take a break?

430
00:19:26,990 --> 00:19:28,429
You're seriously
gonna quit surgery?

431
00:19:28,514 --> 00:19:30,021
I need some good things
in my life.

432
00:19:30,106 --> 00:19:31,302
And babies are good.

433
00:19:31,403 --> 00:19:33,326
You realize OB
is all about moms, yeah?

434
00:19:33,410 --> 00:19:36,068
Yeah, who are happy
because they're having babies.

435
00:19:36,152 --> 00:19:38,288
Not having my own
any time soon...

436
00:19:38,372 --> 00:19:39,332
Fingers crossed.

437
00:19:39,416 --> 00:19:40,927
...or maybe ever,

438
00:19:41,012 --> 00:19:42,843
so I might as well hang out
with some others.

439
00:19:42,928 --> 00:19:44,801
I got like 15 of them
at home.

440
00:19:44,886 --> 00:19:47,170
- Hang out with those.
- It's so unfair!

441
00:19:47,255 --> 00:19:49,647
You and Amelia
didn't even want a baby,

442
00:19:49,731 --> 00:19:51,889
and then you got one
and neither of you died.

443
00:19:51,974 --> 00:19:53,950
Oh, poor you.

444
00:19:54,035 --> 00:19:57,139
You're young and single
and dating a plastic surgeon.

445
00:19:57,224 --> 00:19:58,687
No, we're not...
not dating. It's just sex.

446
00:19:58,771 --> 00:20:00,576
- And you can still work.
- Oh.

447
00:20:00,661 --> 00:20:02,877
Last time
my life sucked this bad,

448
00:20:02,961 --> 00:20:05,271
I quit medicine
and moved to Venice Beach.

449
00:20:05,356 --> 00:20:06,959
Ah, yes.
The bike shop, right?

450
00:20:07,044 --> 00:20:08,318
Heaven.

451
00:20:08,403 --> 00:20:10,102
Jackson wants to
run away to the woods.

452
00:20:10,186 --> 00:20:11,271
Oh, nice.
Can I come?

453
00:20:11,356 --> 00:20:12,577
No, that would defeat
the purpose.

454
00:20:12,661 --> 00:20:14,411
What is
the purpose?

455
00:20:14,495 --> 00:20:16,500
- You kidding? Escape. Outta here.
- Mm.

456
00:20:16,677 --> 00:20:19,092
Escape from pain and rage
and responsibility.

457
00:20:19,177 --> 00:20:20,460
Escape from humanity.

458
00:20:20,544 --> 00:20:22,068
I mean,
trees don't murder people.

459
00:20:22,153 --> 00:20:23,507
- Trees are not racist.
- Mm-hmm.

460
00:20:23,591 --> 00:20:25,378
Trees do not
politicize a disease

461
00:20:25,462 --> 00:20:26,466
and convince
millions of people

462
00:20:26,550 --> 00:20:27,811
not to protect themselves
and others

463
00:20:27,895 --> 00:20:30,166
by using a simple piece of damn
fabric on their faces, so...

464
00:20:30,250 --> 00:20:31,927
Trees don't even
have faces.

465
00:20:32,012 --> 00:20:33,498
You know what?
Maybe you can come.

466
00:20:35,168 --> 00:20:36,389
Ohh!

467
00:20:38,153 --> 00:20:39,653
<i>♪ Oh</i>

468
00:20:41,696 --> 00:20:44,436
Uh, primary repair
of the stomach...

469
00:20:44,521 --> 00:20:46,163
...diaphragm, splenectomy,

470
00:20:46,247 --> 00:20:48,537
and repair
of ventricular injury...

471
00:20:48,622 --> 00:20:50,224
all intact.

472
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:53,536
Ultimately died
from coagulopathy.

473
00:20:53,621 --> 00:20:55,930
- Like I told you.
- Well, now we have it in writing.

474
00:20:56,185 --> 00:20:58,529
Which will make
the M&M go smoothly.

475
00:20:58,614 --> 00:20:59,804
The M&M?

476
00:21:00,021 --> 00:21:01,941
Bailey, what in the hell
are you trying to prove?

477
00:21:02,060 --> 00:21:03,724
It's Andrew DeLuca.

478
00:21:03,809 --> 00:21:06,255
He gave five years of his life
to this hospital.

479
00:21:06,411 --> 00:21:07,903
We own him due diligence.

480
00:21:07,988 --> 00:21:10,558
What about what you owe to your
doctors that are still here?

481
00:21:10,753 --> 00:21:13,458
The ones who've sacrificed
their lives to fight a pandemic,

482
00:21:13,708 --> 00:21:16,385
who hardly sleep or eat
or even shower,

483
00:21:16,470 --> 00:21:18,431
who see their families
on screens...

484
00:21:18,638 --> 00:21:21,756
Their faces are full of bruises
because of the damn PPE,

485
00:21:21,841 --> 00:21:24,115
and now you want them
to sit in front of a computer

486
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,896
and be grilled
on whether they messed up

487
00:21:25,997 --> 00:21:27,701
trying to save
one of their own?

488
00:21:27,785 --> 00:21:29,486
Let them grieve,
for God's sake!

489
00:21:37,446 --> 00:21:39,536
You are causing me harm.

490
00:21:40,189 --> 00:21:44,185
You are causing harm
to Hunt and Altman.

491
00:21:44,846 --> 00:21:48,548
DeLuca was a victim
of a horrible crime,

492
00:21:48,632 --> 00:21:50,778
and he lost
too much blood.

493
00:21:50,927 --> 00:21:54,685
No mistakes were made,
no stitch was missed.

494
00:21:54,769 --> 00:21:56,623
And the mere suggestion
that any of us

495
00:21:56,708 --> 00:21:59,903
didn't do everything possible
to save his life...

496
00:22:02,342 --> 00:22:04,764
...it's a pain
I wouldn't put on anyone.

497
00:22:17,531 --> 00:22:19,646
I want you closer.

498
00:22:19,822 --> 00:22:22,364
Could you please
just come here?

499
00:22:24,015 --> 00:22:26,904
Do you remember when
you were trying to teach Zola

500
00:22:26,989 --> 00:22:28,284
how to ride a bike?

501
