664
00:30:22,265 --> 00:30:23,661
and that she needs
time with you, too,

665
00:30:23,745 --> 00:30:27,186
because she's the oldest
and she's your favorite.

666
00:30:27,270 --> 00:30:29,232
Zola.

667
00:30:29,316 --> 00:30:32,714
Then I hear a click and a lock,
but we're in darkness.

668
00:30:32,798 --> 00:30:35,543
Can't tell who has it,
'cause I can't see a face.

669
00:30:35,627 --> 00:30:39,111
But then I hear a voice,
and it's the oldest one.

670
00:30:39,195 --> 00:30:41,461
And she's
sittin' in the dark.

671
00:30:41,545 --> 00:30:43,376
She's in her closet.

672
00:30:43,460 --> 00:30:45,988
That's where she goes
to write letters to her dad.

673
00:30:46,072 --> 00:30:49,165
And she says,
"I'm really sorry, Mum.

674
00:30:49,249 --> 00:30:51,036
Didn't mean for things
to get so violent.

675
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:53,996
Ellis can be
truly infuriating."

676
00:30:56,125 --> 00:30:58,261
They need you, Grey.

677
00:30:58,345 --> 00:30:59,654
I know.

678
00:30:59,738 --> 00:31:01,090
They need you to fight.

679
00:31:01,174 --> 00:31:05,660
<i>♪ My thoughts don't drift</i>

680
00:31:05,744 --> 00:31:08,194
